    Spring MVC(MODEL VIEW CONTROLLER)
This is a framework within the spring eco system, that is designed for building web application.
-How the web works
When you open a website in your browser
Your computer called the "client"
sends a request to another computer called the "server"
the "server" sends back a response which the browser displays as a webpage.
This communication happens using a protocol called "HTTP"(Hypertext transfer protocol).
Http: This is a set of rules that computers follow to send and receive data over the internet.
Meaning: everytime i visit a website,
the browser sends an http request to fetch the page
the server processes the request and sends back an http response with the content of the page.
    HTTP REQUEST contains the following
-method: GET, POST etc
-url: The address of the resource you are requesting
-Headers: User-Agent, Authentication
-Body(Optional): send data to the server eg when you submit a form.
    HTTP response contains the following
-Status: 200(Ok), 404(Not Found)
-Headers: that includes meta data about the response eg Content-Type Json
-Body: web page, data
    HTML(HyperText Markup Language)
This defines the structure of a web page.
There are two ways a webpage can be generated and sent to the user.
1)The server generates the entire web page before sending it to the browser
This is called Server Side Rendering (SSR)
2)The server sends the raw data and the client (browser) generates the page itself.
This is called Client side rendering (CSR)
    JSON(JavaScript Object Notation)
The server can also send data to the client as JSON
The client takes the data and dynamically creates the web page
we use React, Angular, View to take care of page rendering.
    APIs(Application Programming Interface)
This type of interaction where the server provides raw data
instead of a full page is made possible through something called an APIs.
API: Ths is a way for applications to communicate with eachother
ie: The backend(server) exposes an API and the frontend like REACT consumes the API to render web pages.
APIs are not only for frontend applications.
    Spring boot
With spring boot we can build two types of backends(server) that is SSR or CSR.

-Spring Mvc: This is  a framework for building web apps
It gives us all the tools to handle HTTP requests, Generate web pages, return data to clients.
It is part of the spring eco system and spring boot makes it easy to use.
It is a popular design pattern for organizing our code.
Model: This handles the Data and business logic
View: This is what the user sees eg html page
Controller: This is the middle man, it takes a request, processes it and sends a response.
When we annotate a class with a @Controller annotation, we are making the class a bean
Meaning : So when the application starts, spring creates an instance of the class and manages it.

@Controller: This annotation is used to define the controller
Java creates a bean because of the annotation
bean: This is an object that spring creates and manages for you.

    View templates
Template engine: A tool that allows to create dynamic web pages by embedding variables and logic inside HTML files.
    Types of template engines
-JSP(JavaServer Pages)
-Freemaker
-Mustache
-Thymeleaf
Thymeleaf: This has some attributes that enhances html
With these attributes you can render content dynamically.
    Passing Data To Views
We can pass data from our controller to view using model

-Build modern apis
    REST-Representational State Transfer
A set of rules that define how applications should communicate over HTTP.
Api: is an interface that allow application to talk to eachother.
RESTful APIs: is an API that follow a certain rule.
@RestController: We use this annotation when building an api.
spring automatically converts our java objects to json object.
With apis other applications can consume our data and use them however they want.

